Why Do Lobsters Turn Red When Cooked?

00:00:08.540 --> 00:00:16.230
Typically, the exoskeleton of most crustaceans
has a blue-green to grayish color and sometimes

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:21.660
they appear a brown or olive green, with just
a hint of red; with a few exceptions like

00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:24.140
the blue and yellow lobsters and crabs.

00:00:24.140 --> 00:00:29.429
The exoskeletons of such creatures are made
up of several pigments, one of which is a

00:00:29.429 --> 00:00:34.080
carotenoid called astaxanthin, which provides
its reddish coloring (astaxanthin is the same

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:36.110
carotene that gives salmon its color).

00:00:36.110 --> 00:00:39.770
At normal temperatures and when alive (in
